Class YamlConstructorForProtoBuf

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.yaml.snakeyaml.constructor.BaseConstructor
      • org.yaml.snakeyaml.constructor.SafeConstructor
        • org.yaml.snakeyaml.constructor.Constructor
          • app.coronawarn.server.services.distribution.assembly.appconfig.parsing.YamlConstructorForProtoBuf
  • public class YamlConstructorForProtoBuf
extends org.yaml.snakeyaml.constructor.Constructor
    This Constructor implementation grants SnakeYaml compliance with the generated proto Java classes. SnakeYaml expects the Java properties to have the same name as the yaml properties. But the generated Java classes' properties have an added suffix of '_'. In addition, this implementation also allows snake case in the YAML (for better readability), as the Java properties are transformed to camel case.
